      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "A telegram has been received\nby A. M. Doland, chairman of\nthe interstate commerce COM\nmittee of the cham\nber of commerce, from J. 3.\nCampbell, secretary of the Mer-\nchants association, now in\nWashington, D. c., on the\n\"short haul, long haul\" bill, in\nwhich he says that he has inter-\nviewed the members of the in\nterstate commerce commission\nand that they have told him\nthat the Spokane rate case will\nbe finally passed upon before\nthe adjournment of the COM\nmission for the summer vaca-\nton, June is.\n\n\nThis places the final decis-\nion Of this famous case less\nthan 90 days distant."
    }
  ]
